/* CA Specification format
	Lattice: 
		- Structure: Euclidean ( one dimensional | two dimesional )
		Hexagonal ( This property depend of the neighbohood )
		- Size: "The maximun size can be caculated by the available free memory"
			* X dimension
			* Y dimension
		- Boundary Conditions: ( fixed | toroidal (all matrix | some sides))
		this condition is given on the rule
	
	Neighoorhood: ( Neuman | Moore | hexagonal |custome )
	
	Set of states: 
		- Type: ( structure | int | bool | bit | array | ... )
		- Initial state ( function | initial config matrx )

	Transition function: ( function | mapping table )
		- identify with changes depend directli of the transition function

	CA Running parameters:
		- number of generations ( int )
		- upto some function condition ( function )
	HINT : CONSIDER A C TEMPLATE FOR THIS POURPUSES
*/